                <head>The Future of the South</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>Edward A. Pollard</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>Argues that "there is a hopeful future for the South," but only if the
                    South "can reassert some of her former spirit" instead of "yielding
                    unconditional obedience" to injustices like the test-oath.</summary>
                <note/>
